<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,158,1157]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,266,292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[370,599,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis box="[370,599,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Callitriche stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[968,1177,266,292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis box="[968,1089,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1350,1451,267,293]" name="Morocco" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Morocco</collectingCountry>
except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[217,344,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[217,344,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the combination of the large fruit that are greyish-brown when mature, and large anthers with yellow pollen. It can only reliably be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[790,919,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[790,919,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the looped testa of the fruit, however most healthy plants of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[331,458,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[331,458,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will have leaves with more than seven parallel veins, whereas the leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[1317,1451,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis box="[1317,1451,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have fewer veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,158,1157]" box="[189,1290,446,472]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,446,472]" pageId="12" pageNumber="65">Illustrations:</emphasis>
